name: Internet of Things and real-timecomputing
description: We live in a data-driven world, where multiple devices around us measure all kind of physical magnitudes and communicate to each other. In order to be useful, these devices must be able to operate in real time. The talk will provide an introduction on the constraints that real time computing present for IoT devices and will describe real-time operating systems and what we can expect from them.
